/44/37a/644" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/dan-morrison/40/42b/408" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/cauvery-muthanna/44/5b1/162" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/dan-morrison/0/42b/a16" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/colin-tynan/6b/8a7/a38" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/matt-davis/0/626/a67" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/tristram-colville-foley/2a/955/26b" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/dan-morrison/14/127/a11" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/david-owens/2b/2a3/372" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/dianne-saffery/6/b8b/656" , "http://www.linkedin.com/in/danielmorrison1984" , "http://www.linkedin.com/pub/cho-oliver/24/178/144" , "http://www.linkedin.com/in/danieldmorrison"] , "image_url" : "http://m.c.lnkd.licdn.com/mpr/mpr/shrink_200_200/p/2/005/04a/0a4/066510d.jpg" , "given_name" : "Dan" , "full_name" : "Dan Morrison" , "experience" : [ { "end" : "000000" , "description" : "BLOTT WORKS is a small independent design studio, based in the north of England, producing limited-edition hand-engineered functional sculpture. Established by Dan Morrison and Andy Plant, two artist/engineers and long time collaborators, now launching their first products: http://www.blottworks.com" , "title" : "Founder/Designer" , "start" : "201201" , "location" : "United Kingdom" , "duration" : "000211" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "BLOTT WORKS"}]} , { "end" : "Present" , "description" : "Throughout the last 25 years I have been a regular freelance collaborator on projects with art production company IOU - as sound artist/composer, as deviser and maker, and as performer. IOU is an organisation with 37 years experience making original work across art-forms including: sound, video and sculptural installations, site specific performance, music, touring theatre, interactive digital works and virtual worlds. The company is recognised for creating work with a distinctive style, both intimate and large scale, commonly a collision of the familiar and the mysterious, often darkly humorous. \"IOU occupies a position in the contemporary arts and performance arena where it is considered to be a model of excellence both nationally and internationally, a position it rightly deserves. The often surreal and fantastic narratives are a means of transporting the audience to a world of possibilities which are dreamlike yet present opportunities for contemplating the ordinary and familiar things around us. This is an important part of IOU's aesthetic approach and cultural identity. On reviewing thirty years of work, you begin to appreciate how everything is beautifully made, from costumes to machines, revealing an in-depth understanding of art, materials and mechanics.\" Quote from Russell Roberts, Head of Photography & Senior Curator of Photographs, National Museum of Photography, Film & TV http://www.ioutheatre.org/ http://danmorrison.co.uk/ It is through this work with IOU that I first met Andy Plant and with whom I now run BLOTT WORKS." , "title" : "Deviser/Composer/Maker" , "start" : "March 1990" , "location" : "Halifax, United Kingdom" , "duration" : "24 years 9 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "IOU"}]} , { "end" : "September 2012" , "title" : "Funeral Director" , "start" : "November 2009" , "location" : "Todmorden" , "duration" : "2 years 11 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "J&C Warburton"}]} , { "end" : "November 2009" , "description" : "I was recruited first as an Account Manager, managing web developments for various big brands, working with our technical and creative teams and the client's commissioning teams. During this time I helped Travelodge move from 6% online sales to over 85%, completely transforming their business. I then worked as Account Director, managing the team of account managers and project managers, responsible for client relationships, for profitability of accounts, and the quality of our work." , "title" : "Account Director" , "start" : "September 2006" , "location" : "Leeds, United Kingdom" , "duration" : "3 years 3 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "Sense Internet" , "profile_url" : "http://www.linkedin.com/company/53088"}]} , { "end" : "September 2001" , "description" : "protoLAB was a Technology Lab focussing on the conceptualisation and prototyping of new technological solutions. I was brought in to drive the design and piloting of a highly secure networked resource for children living in care, available via handhelds, Web TV, Kiosk, Games Consoles, PCs etc. This involved analysing and refining the client proposal, investigating possible technologies, designing and building a prototype system, and specifying approaches for the follow-on phase. The prototype was built as an intranet using HTML, ASP/JavaScript, IIS, SQLServer, mdaemon, JetForms, eShare, Flash/ActionScript, video, and audio streams." , "title" : "Consultant" , "start" : "January 2001" , "location" : "Brighton, United Kingdom" , "duration" : "9 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "protoLAB Ltd"}]} , { "end" : "July 2000" , "description" : "I joined the company as the first employee to aid the three founders in developing the business: I was instrumental in growing the company from this up to 35 employees plus a large freelance pool of designers and programmers. Okupi was set-up to develop online social environments, specialising in 3D and virtual spaces. We also developed other online and new media applications as part of this work. I was responsible for the production side of the business and managing the team (essentially inward facing), and the sales side (i;e; the outward facing role) was handled by our managing director, Simon Warner-Bore." , "title" : "Director" , "start" : "April 1997" , "location" : "London, United Kingdom" , "duration" : "3 years 4 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "Okupi Ltd"}]} , { "end" : "April 1997" , "description" : "Joined the company when there were only 30 of us. I initially worked as a C++ programmer building client/server applications for for brands including Financial Times, Plan International, McKinsey & Company and Nynex Communications" , "title" : "Senior Developer & Project Manager" , "start" : "October 1994" , "location" : "London, United Kingdom" , "duration" : "2 years 7 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "Quidnunc" , "profile_url" : "http://www.linkedin.com/company/15211"}]} , { "end" : "December 1994" , "description" : "Developing an Intelligent 3D drawing package for architects and engineers using C++ and HyperTalk on a Mac." , "title" : "Software Developer/Researcher" , "start" : "April 1992" , "location" : "London, United Kingdom" , "duration" : "2 years 9 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "Bartlett School of Architecture, University College London" , "profile_url" : "http://www.linkedin.com/company/718739"}]} , { "end" : "April 1992" , "description" : "During this time I worked with many other artists and performers operating on the edges of their field, devising and touring various shows, installations and ensembles. From John Peel Sessions to the Royal Festival Hall, from Edinburgh Festival to Blue Peter, I could be seen and heard in all sorts of interesting places. I also taught in schools, privately and through workshops." , "title" : "Musician/Creative" , "start" : "August 1983" , "location" : "Royal Leamington Spa" , "duration" : "8 years 9 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "Rattlentoot"}]} , { "end" : "October 1988" , "description" : "Hard-hitting underground band of the mid-eighties. Record deal with independent label Ron Johnson Records (Long Eaton), recorded two John Peel sessions and toured throughout the UK (and later Europe). A track appeared on a recent CD release entitled \"The Best of British Underground 1983-1988\". The band has recently reformed with three of the original members." , "title" : "Musician" , "start" : "March 1984" , "location" : "Royal Leamington Spa" , "duration" : "4 years 8 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "Jackdaw with Crowbar"}]} , { "end" : "July 1987" , "description" : "Teaching drums and percussion to individuals and groups in schools around Warwickshire. Played in the Warwickshire Multicultural Ensemble, taking world music to young people, as part of this role." , "title" : "Peripatetic Teacher and Musician" , "start" : "September 1985" , "location" : "Warwickshire" , "duration" : "1 year 11 months" , "organization" : [ { "name" : "Warwickshire County Council" , "profile_url" : "http://www.linkedin.com/company/166871"}]}] , "education" : [ { "start" : "199300" , "end" : "199400" , "name" : "University College London, U. of London" , "degrees" : [ "Master of Science (MSc)" , "Computer Science" , "" , "Distinction"]} , { "start" : "1980" , "end" : "1983" , "name" : "University of Warwick" , "degrees" : [ "Engineering Design & Appropriate Technology" , "Engineering Design" , "" , "BSc (Hons)"]} , { "start" : "1971" , "end" : "1977" , "name" : "Ludlow Grammar School" , "degrees" : [ "O-levels and A-levels"]}] , "canonical_url" : "http://uk.linkedin.com/in/danofblottworks" , "projects" : [ { "date" : "September 2011" , "description" : "Composer Volatile Light is a mesmerising sound and light installation, originally commissioned by Junction Goole. Featuring an array of specially made machines, LED lights will be attached to rotating arms, levers and cranks to weave a series of eccentric curves, sweeping arcs and hectic scribbles in the darkened gallery space. Utilising an innovative combination of computer software, the lights will then be transformed into a complex mixture of overlapping light trails and patterns. Audiences will experience an intimate, all enveloping combination of light and sound by placing themselves at the centre of a miniature, wrap around universe of moving lights and sounds." , "title" : "Volatile Light (Link)"} , { "date" : "September 2010" , "description" : "Composer Presented at Junction Goole, September 2010, Airborne began a project to capture sounds produced in the natural world through basic scientific experiments and then manipulate them into a musical soundscape. Over the course of three days, IOU set up and executed a series of experiments using natural materials. These experiments included boiling mud, snapping slate, dripping water onto a hot plate and fast heating liquid nitrogen. The resulting sounds were captured as the experiments unfolded and manipulated to make a unique, ethereal composition. Also included IOU creative sound and composition workshops with school children at Peking University's School of Computer Engineering, Beijing, working from the principles used to create Airborne. Also ran workshops at schools in Oxford and Goole." , "title" : "Airborne (Link)"} , { "date" : "March 2010 October 2013" , "description" : "Composer and sound artist. Long Division is a sound installation made specially for the walled garden of the University of Oxford Botanic Garden. As the surrounding church bells chime seven, a sequence of sixty whispered exchanges begins, timed to the divisions of the clock. The whispering phrases gather in intensity second by second creating rhythmic speech patterns that send a wash of sound rippling around the walls. Rising up beneath the voices, a soundscape evolves, resonant of patterns in nature and cycles of growth and decay. The sequence lasts one hour and repeats three times as day merges into night. Long Division was originally commissioned by Oxford Contemporary Music and Oxford Botanic Garden." , "title" : "Long Division (Link)"} , { "date" : "July 2009" , "description" : "Composer Following the death of her goldfish, a couple embark on a quest to transform matter. As they become enmeshed within the mechanics of the universe, they are shadowed by a cluster of ghost-like film technicians who manipulate their progress. IOU's base at Dean Clough has become an eerie film studio where our travelers are seen immersed in their journey unconscious of the paraphernalia that surrounds them. Once the travelers had reached the end of their journey the audience were transported to Beacon Hill, over looking Halifax, for a fantastically normal finale." , "title" : "Electric Field (Link)"} , { "date" : "January 2006 September 2007" , "description" : "Composer An indoor site-specific show for Square Chapel Centre for the Arts in Halifax. A woman awakes to find herself in a vast white desert. The only landmark is a distant dead tree. The only evidence of how she came to be here is a wrecked car. As she begins to piece together her recollections, grotesque figures from childhood stories invade the landscape, intent on preventing her escape." , "title" : "Waylaid (Link)"} , { "date" : "May 2001" , "description" : "Deviser/Performer/Musician A small scale outdoor show toured England. A stretched limousine is cut in half and welded into an enormous, baroque mirror with a pile of kitchen cabinets to create a contraption that becomes the vehicle for a perilous and improbable journey. An outdoor, touring show for festivals, fun-days and many locations." , "title" : "Daylight Nightmare (Link)"} , { "date" : "April 2003" , "description" : "Deviser/Animatronic Controller An outdoor, UK touring spectacular. In a mechanical wild life arena, nocturnal creatures are coming to life! A large scale outdoor show for 2000 people commissioned by Stockton International Riverside Festival and co-commissioned by Bradford International Festival, Big in Falkirk and Streets of Brighton. It was staged at these festivals and at Halifax, Liverpool, and Greenwich. A fuming army of petrol driven insects are in erratic pursuit of a monstrous mechanical egg factory. Venting gooey foam along the way, this towering structure ambles through the audience attempting to keep its precious crop from the clutches of the marauding swarm." , "title" : "Tattoo (Link)"} , { "date" : "November 2000 October 2001" , "description" : "Maker/Performer A large site specific show for Dean Clough Mills in Halifax as part of the Huddersfield Contemporary Music Festival in which the audience moved through different locations around the Mills' complex. Plagued by an infectious collection of characters, our hapless patient encounters unorthodox curative devices, unearthly hospital routines and angelic hallucinations, on a perilous road to a rude awakening. Through a delirious soundscape of music and song, together with an elaborate collection of mechanical apparatus and alarming concoctions, we enter an unfathomable system that mirrors the uncertainties of illnesses and cures. Cure explores the curious territory between sickness and health, where mental and physical battles are fought. A darkly humorous look at life on the edge." , "title" : "Cure (Link)"} , { "date" : "May 2008" , "description" : "Performer Presented in China at the Vis-A-Vis Art Lab at CO2 United Creative Space, Beijing. Explore an unnerving environment where life is suspended in a series of never-ending cliff hangers as IOU presents Eye Witness - a darkly humorous investigation at the point of no return. Witness intriguing scenes from ill fated adventures as a succession of characters are caught in a continuous loop from which there seems to be no escape. Each looks to you for help, but, trapped in another dimension, you can only observe....." , "title" : "Eye Witness (Link)"} , { "date" : "May 1998" , "description" : "Project Manager (and sound designer) We were commissioned to create an online shared 3D replica of the Richard Rogers building in London, to form part of their corporate web site, to allow visitors to the site to experience walking around the inside of the building." , "title" : "Virtual Lloyds of London"} , { "date" : "March 1999" , "description" : "Project manager/Creative advisor Okupi was asked to create a multi-tiered virtual world, with customisable avatars, for teenage members of their web site, with multiple zones and opportunities to safely interact, hang-out/look cool and listen to music." , "title" : "Trouble TV - teenage online 3D social space"} , { "date" : "January 1999" , "description" : "Project Manager We were asked to produce an online 3D reproduction of the iconic London club so that music fans from around the world could socialise and get a taste of the venue and listen to tunes of their choosing." , "title" : "Virtual Ministry of Sound"} , { "date" : "December 1996" , "description" : "Project Manager Cable & Wireless were merging with Nynex communications and asked Quidnunc to consolidate their systems and data, and to provide data visualisation tools." , "title" : "Data Warehousing for Cable & Wireless"} , { "date" : "May 1995" , "description" : "User Interface Designer Quidnunc was tasked with developing an worldwide system that Plan could use to co-ordinate all their activities across the developing and developed worlds. We had to produce something that was easy to use for both their admin staff and all their field staff across the world. This demanded an architecture and interface that was clear and functional across many diverse cultures and skill levels." , "title" : "Plan International - Child Sponsorship System"} , { "date" : "May 1994" , "description" : "Programmer We developed their main remote access information tool using C++/Oracle to build a networked system on HTTP/FTP/Telnet protocols, pulling in real time financial data from a variety of sources. This was in the days before everything was available on the web - one of the pioneering systems!" , "title" : "Online Real-time Financial Information Service for Financial Times"} , { "date" : "March 1993" , "description" : "Programmer We developed and rolled out a networked software application that the McKinsey consultants could use as their primary PA tool." , "title" : "Consultants tool for McKinsey & Company"} , { "date" : "January 1991" , "description" : "Maker The odd couple inhabiting a Swiss-style weatherhouse can never meet. Their doomed love affair is frustrated by the weather, the house and a radio-controlled dog. A ten minute made-for-film version of the production completed in a mix of live action and animated sequences. The film Weatherhouse was developed with film maker Joanna Woodward for the BBC2, 10' x 10' series." , "title" : "The Weatherhouse Film (Link)"} , { "date" : "April 1992" , "description" : "Maker/Composer/Musician/Performer A new outdoor Summer touring show. In the garden all is well. In the house all is not well...Leather-skinned gardeners tend singing hedges, giant furniture tours the ground and pest control is carried to extremes. 2 x Table toured nationwide." , "title" : "2 X Table (Link)"} , { "date" : "October 1990" , "description" : "Puppeteer/Maker The odd couple inhabiting a Swiss-style weatherhouse could never meet; the woman came out when it was sunny, the man came out when it rained. A bijou residence with reluctant inhabitants, skewed views, wicked weather and wall-to-wall delights. The wry chronicle of Roy, Ruby and Rover told in tangled tales and haunting music. Their doomed love affair is frustrated by the weather, the house and a radio-controlled dog. Their furious flow of startling songs and stories keeps the changeable fronts and squalls at bay. In the garden, Roy dreams of turning potatoes into diamonds, whilst Ruby finds only a pot of red herrings at the end of the rainbow. Rover, meanwhile, is in the doghouse. This indoor show toured England." , "title" : "Weatherhouse (Link)"} , { "date" : "March 1990 September 1992" , "description" : "Maker/Composer/Musician/Performer Full Tilt was a touring piece that visited outdoor events throughout the Summer. An extraordinary show of live music machines, quite a large pair of shoes, war and peace. The king and queen sit high in their howdah surrounded by a brigade of watchful eyes. Live music strikes up from a royal vehicle - a wealth of sounds from a multitude of acoustic instruments and mechanical inventions. In the tilt yard below, two combatants are made ready for a 